WEBVTT

00:02.502 --> 00:04.137
I don't even know where
her parents live.

00:05.088 --> 00:06.232
It's a place back east, I think.

00:06.256 --> 00:07.233
Charlie...

00:07.257 --> 00:08.651
And I tried calling some
old friends of ours,

00:08.675 --> 00:09.976
but nobody kept in
touch with her.

00:10.885 --> 00:12.687
She just split.

00:12.887 --> 00:14.824
I know, we've been
over this but...

00:14.848 --> 00:16.075
It doesn't make any sense.

00:16.099 --> 00:17.284
She blows back into my life

00:17.308 --> 00:18.744
and asks me to help
take care of my kid.

00:18.768 --> 00:19.662
My kid.

00:19.686 --> 00:21.654
And then she takes off like
that doesn't even matter.

00:25.358 --> 00:26.585
She must have changed her mind.

00:26.609 --> 00:28.838
Well, that's not her right!
She can't do that.

00:28.862 --> 00:30.288
How can she just do that?

00:31.281 --> 00:32.842
I know I'm not the
greatest person

00:32.866 --> 00:34.125
to be saying this, but...

00:36.995 --> 00:38.296
If you think about it...

00:39.080 --> 00:40.506
I don't know, but...

00:41.041 --> 00:42.717
Maybe it's easier this way.

00:43.418 --> 00:44.886
Easier for who?

00:46.838 --> 00:48.014
Well...

00:48.339 --> 00:49.557
For you.

00:50.258 --> 00:51.559
For me?

00:52.010 --> 00:53.352
Are you kidding?

00:53.845 --> 00:55.938
Okay, for Spencer then.

00:56.014 --> 00:57.700
You said yourself,
you know, before,

00:57.724 --> 00:59.744
that it can't be in
his best interests

00:59.768 --> 01:01.120
to have someone come
in and out of his life

01:01.144 --> 01:02.121
all the time.

01:02.145 --> 01:04.364
It's got to be better than
growing up without a father.

01:04.438 --> 01:05.698
Maybe.

01:06.357 --> 01:07.835
But the more time
you spend with him,

01:07.859 --> 01:09.253
the more you're gonna
fall in love with him,

01:09.277 --> 01:11.204
and the more he'll
fall in love with you.

01:11.404 --> 01:13.790
Who's to say that she
wouldn't take off anyway?

01:17.327 --> 01:18.920
Kirsten, I worry about him.

01:20.413 --> 01:22.256
I know that sounds crazy, but...

01:22.999 --> 01:24.133
I do.

01:25.293 --> 01:26.803
Of course you do.

01:29.255 --> 01:30.473
But...

01:32.342 --> 01:33.778
By leaving like this,

01:33.802 --> 01:35.362
she's telling you

01:35.386 --> 01:38.231
that it's not your
responsibility anymore.

01:38.932 --> 01:40.983
She's letting you
off the hook and...

01:46.272 --> 01:47.907
Maybe that's for the best.

01:50.819 --> 01:52.537
So I'm supposed to just...

01:53.696 --> 01:55.081
forget about him?

01:58.910 --> 02:00.336
How can I do that?

02:04.207 --> 02:05.925
How can I possibly do that?

